 Free for all in Goa
OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENTNew Delhi: Unbelievable but true. When Mohun Bagan and East Bengal visit Goa in the second week of December for their I-League campaign, their matches will be open to the spectators. In a surprising move, the Goa Football Association (GFA) has decided to make the first leg of the I-League a gate-free tournament. Lack of spectators for I-League matches is one of the main reasons to throw the gates open, said GFA secretary Savio Messias. Henceforth, tickets would be sold only for the VIP stands of the Nehru Stadium in Margao, he added. 
